 I doubt this is causing the latest<br />&gt; panics.<br /><br />The 43 and 44 inode.c is new, and I suspect that inode.c is the major<br />problem with the new kernels - and the reason 44 is so much worse is that<br />the dcache changes changed the way the inodes were de-allocated and thus<br />made the problem rear its ugly head..<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
